SIMPLE: settler
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Settler
<hw>Set"tler</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
settles, becomes fixed, established, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Especially, one who establishes himself in a new
region or a colony; a colonist; a planter; <as>as, the first
<ex>settlers</ex> of New England</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which settles or finishes; hence, a blow, etc.,
which settles or decides a contest.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A vessel, as a tub, in which something, as
pulverized ore suspended in a liquid, is allowed to settle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Settling</ent>⟦br⟧
